Wash and dry produce.

Dice @Roma tomato{1}. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}; mince a few slices until you have 2 TBSP (3 TBSP for 4 servings). Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Halve, core, and thinly slice @long green pepper{1} into strips.

== Zesty Rice ==

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Pico de Gallo ==

While rice cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine tomato, minced onion, and juice from half the lime. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

In a separate small bowl, combine @sour cream{4%tablespoon} and 1/4 tsp @Southwest spice blend{1%tbsp} (1/2 tsp for 4 servings; you'll use more in the next step). Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

== Veggies ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add green pepper and cook until slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add sliced onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are browned and tender, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Add half the remaining Southwest Spice (you'll use the rest in the next step), 2 TBSP water (4 TBSP for 4 servings), salt, and pepper. Cook until water has mostly evaporated and veggies are coated, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Turn off heat. Transfer to a #plate{}; cover to keep warm. Wipe out pan.

== Beef ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for veggies over medium-high heat. Add @ground beef{10%ounce} and cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> TIP: If there's excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.

Stir in @Tex-Mex paste{1} and remaining Southwest Spice until combined. Add 1/4 cup water (1/3 cup for 4 servings); simmer until mixture is reduced and saucy, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

Remove from heat and stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4) until melted. Season with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in lime zest and season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between #bowls{} and top with beef mixture, veggies, @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup}, pico de gallo, and crema. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.